13/12/2005
TEL AVIV, Israel -- Prime Minister Ariel Sharon and Macedonian counterpart Vlado Buckovski agreed on Monday (12 December) to enhance bilateral ties, especially co-operation in the agricultural, telecommunications, healthcare and cultural sectors.
Buckovski is in Israel, marking ten years of bilateral ties.
In other news, Macedonia and Albania signed an agreement Monday on co-operation in the field of education, science and technology.
Albanian Minister of Education and Science Genc Pollo sealed it with visiting Macedonian counterpart Azis Polozhani.
(Albanian News - 13/12/05;
Telma TV, Makfax, Macedonian Government Web site, Israeli Foreign Ministry press release, Albanian Government Web site - 12/12/05)
